What I Would Add as a New Work Order
This proposal is significant enough that I would not fold it into the existing WO-2001–2010 series. Those work orders establish the epistemic foundation (CanonicalEvent, IdentityKernel, EvidenceGraph, Decision Compiler). What you're describing is the next architectural layer that governs evidence certification.

I would define a new work order:

WO-2011 — Happy Path Certification Engine (HPCE)

Its responsibilities would include:

HP Qualification Pipeline: Classify evidence into HP-0 through HP-3 before it reaches the Decision Compiler.

Structural Confirmation Decomposition: Replace a monolithic SCS with independently calculated dimensions (Identity, Independence, Persistence, Coverage, Agreement, Recency, Source Reliability).

Evidence Adversarial Validation: Execute domain-specific stress injections against candidate Happy Paths.

Counterfeit Difficulty Index (CDI): Quantify how difficult it would be for an adversary to fabricate the observed evidence constellation.

Temporal HP Decay Engine: Continuously re-evaluate HP status as evidence ages or contradictory signals emerge.

Decision Compiler Integration Contract: Ensure the compiler consumes certified evidence and resilience metrics rather than assigning HP labels itself.

This preserves the architectural invariant established in WO-2001 through WO-2010:

Evidence is validated before it is interpreted.

The Decision Compiler remains a reasoning engine—not a truth arbiter. The HP Certification Engine becomes the formal gatekeeper that certifies whether an evidence constellation has earned the designation of a resilient, structurally supported Happy Path. I think that separation strengthens the architecture considerably and keeps the epistemic boundaries clean.





